channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: NEW: Video of Trump Assassination Attempt Emerges Showing Terrified Crowd Running As Shots Ring Out
Vulnerable House Dem dodges question on VP Harris' record as 'border czar': 'Don’t know who Kamala Harris is'
item.description: Vulnerable Democrat Rep. Emilia Sykes dodged questions about Vice President Harris' record on the border when confronted shortly after endorsing her for president.

item.title: Security Fears Spike as Protests Try to Disrupt Netanyahu Speech
item.description: A pro-Palestinian protest Tuesday at a U.S. House office building has sparked security concerns among lawmakers ahead of Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's speech, Axios reported.

item.title: On 'The View,' Kamala Harris Is a 'Moderate,' She Isn't a 'Leftist' - and the Cow Jumped Over the Moon
Kamala Harris’ husband Doug Emhoff responds to Trump's attacks on her: 'That's all he’s got?'
item.description: Second gentleman Doug Emhoff responded after former President Trump criticized his wife, Vice President Kamala Harris, after the launch of her presidential campaign.

item.title: Rep. Jordan to Newsmax: Lies Forced Out USSS Director
item.description: House Judiciary Committee Chair Jim Jordan, R-Ohio, said there were a litany of failures that forced Kimberly Cheatle to resign as Secret Service director but that one stood out from all the rest: what happened after the assassination attempt on former President Donald Trump.

item.title: WATCH: Grassley Shares Incredible Bodycam Footage From Roof Where Shooter Perched at Trump Rally
Steven Pinker: Young people sick and tired of being told, 'you can't say that, you can't think that' on campus
item.description: Dr. Steven Pinker offers a robust defense of Enlightenment values, liberalism, rationality, and market economies, while championing academic freedom on college campuses.

item.title: Mike Huckabee to Newsmax: Harris Unlikely to Connect With Voters
item.description: Even though Democrats are rallying around Vice President Kamala Harris as the party's presumptive presidential nominee, former Arkansas Gov. Mike Huckabee said it doesn't mean she is going to be a formidable opponent to former President Donald Trump in November.

item.title: WATCH: Schumer's Embarrassing 'Clap' Moment for Harris, As He Even Has Trouble With Her Name
Biden set to address nation after pressured exit from 2024 race
item.description: President Biden is expected to address the nation for the first time since dropping out of the 2024 race in an address from the Oval Office on Wednesday evening.

item.title: Musk Says He Never Said He'll Donate $45M Per Month to Trump
item.description: Tesla CEO Elon Musk said in a post on X on Tuesday that he never said he was donating $45 million per month to Republican Donald Trump.This is a developing story....

item.title: 'Not George Washington': DeSantis Nukes Absurd Dem Narrative of 'Selfless' Biden Withdrawing From Race
Secret Service failures during Trump rally spur concerns for Netanyahu visit, McCaul says
item.description: House Foreign Affairs Committee Chairman Michael McCaul spoke with Fox News Digital after touring the site of the failed assassination attempt against former President Trump.

item.title: BLM Demands DNC Primary After Harris 'Nomination'
item.description: Black Lives Matter (BLM) has called on the Democratic National Committee (DNC) to hold an immediate nationwide virtual primary following Vice President Kamala Harris' claim of securing enough delegates for the Democratic presidential nomination.
